Ghana’s Akwatia Mine to Produce 1 Million Carats, Graphic Says

-- B y   E k o w   D o n t o h
-- 
2011-08-24T10:29:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/ghana-s-akwatia-mine-to-produce-1-million-carats-graphic-says.html
Great Consolidated Diamonds Ltd., a
Ghanaian mining company, is investing $100 million to restart
operations at the Akwatia mine in the country’s Eastern Region,
the  Daily Graphic reported , citing Vice President John Mahama.  The mine is expected to produce 1 million carats of the
gems annually within five years and will provide more than 2,500
jobs, the Accra-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ekow Dontoh in Accra at 
 edontoh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  